{"name": "mrio-common-metadata", "metadata": {"name": "mrio-common-metadata", "version": "0.2.1", "classifiers": ["Intended Audience :: Developers", "Intended Audience :: End Users/Desktop", "Intended Audience :: Science/Research", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: MacOS :: MacOS X", "Operating System :: Microsoft :: Windows", "Operating System :: POSIX", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Information Analysis", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Mathematics", "Topic :: Scientific/Engineering :: Visualization"], "home_page": "https://github.com/brightway-lca/mrio_common_metadata", "license": "BSD 3-clause", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Common Datapackage schema and utilities for MRIO tables", "upload_time": 1694787671}, "documentation": ["# mrio_common_metadata\n\n`mrio_common_metadata` provides three things:\n\n* A guide on how the [Data Package](https://frictionlessdata.io/specs/data-package/) and [Table Schema](https://frictionlessdata.io/specs/table-schema/) specifications can be used to make MRIO table more consistently formatted and easier to use.\n* Translations of some common MRIO tables to this format\n* Utility code to help make the previous two objectives possible\n\n# Separating data and metadata\n\nMRIO tables are often given with weird offsets, and multiple or mixed column/row labels, e.g.\n\n![Worksheet with column labels as rows](docs/images/worksheet-1.png)\n\n![Worksheet with multiple column and row labels](docs/images/worksheet-2.png)\n\nWorking with this type of data requires writing custom code each time. It's a pain. The biggest problem is the mixing of two data types: The metdata on what each row and column represent, and the numerical table that forms the main body of the worksheet. `mrio_common_metadata` takes the position that these two data streams should be stored separately. It also requires that data be stored in common formats (compressed CSV) with metadata that meets the `Data Package` specification.\n\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "mrio_common_metadata.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mrio_common_metadata.utils.md5", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "blocksize", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Generate MD5 hash for file at `filepath`"]}, {"name": "mrio_common_metadata.utils.load_compressed_csv", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mrio_common_metadata.utils.load_compressed_csv_as_dataframe", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "exiobase_metadata", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mrio_common_metadata.utils.iterate_compressed_csv", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "mrio_common_metadata.conversion.exiobase_3_hybrid_io.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "mrio_common_metadata.conversion.exiobase_3_hybrid_io.utils.read_xlsb", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filepath", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "worksheet", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "mrio_common_metadata.conversion.exiobase_3_hybrid_io.utils.convert_xlsb", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "workbook", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "worksheet", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sourcedir", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "targetdir", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documenta